n","1273–Female":"1273–Overleden","um 1328":"circa 1328","1330":"1330","1273":"1273","1360":"1360","1359":"1359","1326":"1326","1302":"1302","um 1330":"circa 1330","1400":"1400","1300":"1300","1332":"1332","1265":"1265","um 1300":"circa 1300","um 1332":"circa 1332","um 1320":"circa 1320","um 1326":"circa 1326","um 1302":"circa 1302","1328":"1328","Lübeck, Schleswig-Holstein, Deutschland":"Lübeck, Schleswig-Holstein, Duitsland","Greifswald, Vorpommern-Greifswald, Mecklenburg-Vorpommern, Deutschland":"Greifswald, Vorpommern-Greifswald, Mecklenburg-Vorpommern, Duitsland"},"en":{"um 1302–1359":"about 1302–1359","1302–1359":"1302–1359","–Male":"Deceased","1300–1360":"1300–1360","1326–1400":"1326–1400","1328–Female":"1328–Deceased","1330–Male":"1330–Deceased","1332–Male":"1332–Deceased","1265–Male":"1265–Deceased","1273–Female":"1273–Deceased","um 1328":"about 1328","1330":"1330","1273":"1273","1360":"1360","1359":"1359","1326":"1326","1302":"1302","um 1330":"about 1330","1400":"1400","1300":"1300","1332":"1332","1265":"1265","um 1300":"about 1300","um 1332":"about 1332","um 1320":"about 1320","um 1326":"about 1326","um 1302":"about 1302","1328":"1328","Lübeck, Schleswig-Holstein, Deutschland":"Lübeck, Schleswig-Holstein, Germany","Greifswald, Vorpommern-Greifswald, Mecklenburg-Vorpommern, Deutschland":"Greifswald, Vorpommern-Greifswald, Mecklenburg-Vorpommern, Germany","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Quant","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: nickname from Middle English <i>cointe</i>, <i>queynte</i>, <i>quante</i> ‘wise, skilled, clever’, also ‘cunning, crafty’ (Old French <i>cointe</i>, <i>quoint</i>, <i>cuinte</i>). In Devon the name may alternatively be a variant of   Quance   with loss of final <i>-s</i>.","Dutch: nickname from Middle Dutch <i>quant</i> ‘companion, prankster’.","German: variant of   Quandt  , a cognate of 2 above."],"variants":[{"name":"Quance","meanings":["English (Devon): possibly a variant of   Quant  , with excrescent <i>-s</i>.","Americanized form of German   Quantz  ."]},{"name":"Quint","meanings":["English: nickname from Middle English <i>queint(e)</i> ‘wise, prudent; crafty, sly; elegant; vain’ (Old French <i>cointe</i>, <i>cuinte</i>). Compare   Quant  .","German: from the medieval Latin personal name <i>Quintinus</i> (see   Quintin  ), a Christian saint's name.","French: from Middle French <i>quint</i> ‘fifth’, a term used in western France to denote an administrative area consisting of five villages, presumably applied as a metonymic occupational name for the administrator of such an area."]}]},{"name":"Gertrud","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["from <i>gēr</i>, <i>gār</i> ‘spear’ + <i>þrūþ</i> ‘strength’; the name of two famous 13th-century nuns of the Cistercian Abbey of Helfta near Eisleben, whose spiritual writings had a great influence."],"variants":[{"name":"Gertraud","meanings":["from <i>gēr</i>, <i>gār</i> ‘spear’ + <i>þrūþ</i> ‘strength’; the name of two famous 13th-century nuns of the Cistercian Abbey of Helfta near Eisleben, whose spiritual writings had a great influence."]},{"name":"Gertraut","meanings":["from <i>gēr</i>, <i>gār</i> ‘spear’ + <i>þrūþ</i> ‘strength’; the name of two famous 13th-century nuns of the Cistercian Abbey of Helfta near Eisleben, whose spiritual writings had a great influence."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Gertrud Quant was born about 1302, in Greifswald, Vorpommern-Greifswald, Mecklenburg-Vorpommern, Germany, her father, Johann Dictus Quant, was 39 and her mother, Gertraud Quant, was 31. She married Gerhard Bocholt about 1320, in Lübeck, Schleswig-Holstein, Germany. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 2 daughters. She died in 1359, in her hometown, at the age of 58."},"et":{"um 1302–1359":"umbes 1302–1359","1302–1359":"1302–1359","–Male":"Surnud","1300–1360":"1300–1360","1326–1400":"1326–1400","1328